content.text:
**Root cause confirmed and fixed.**

## Summary

The bug: `<%= @vnc_url.to_json %>` in the wait page script block.

`String#to_json` in Rails returns a **non-html_safe** String. ERB's `<%= %>` HTML-escapes it, turning the JSON's wrapping `"` quotes into `&quot;`:

```javascript
// BROKEN — what ERB produced:
var vncUrl = &quot;/vnc/8/vnc.html?path=vnc/8/websockify\u0026autoconnect=true&quot;;
//           ^^^^^^                                                               ^^^^^^
//           HTML entities — JavaScript syntax error!
```

This caused the entire `<script>` block to fail at parse time. `setInterval` was never set up, the status endpoint was never polled, and the wait page always hit the 30-second timeout — every single time.

**Fix:** `<%= raw @vnc_url.to_json %>` — `raw()` bypasses ERB's HTML escaping. Safe because `.to_json` already Unicode-escapes `&`, `<`, `>` to `\u0026`, `\u003c`, `\u003e`.
